                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311020-173-off923 t18311020-173-crimeloc925"></join>, to have a child christened - when I got in, the first thing I saw was the prisoner with his hand in a gentleman's pocket - I went<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183110200069"></xptr>up to him, and took hold of his right arm; he dropped this handkerchief down, and I took it - I went to the gentleman, and asked if he knew he had been robbed - he said No, but he felt, and his handkerchief was gone; we went to the station - the gentleman gave a name and address, but said he did not wish to do any thing to the prisoner; I went to the address, but could not find the gentleman.</p>
